Cook peppers and onions in oil in a heavy bottom pot on medium high heat until softened, about 5 minutes. Add garlic, tomatoes, paprika and cumin. Cook for 2 minutes more. Add rice, broth and chicken and bring to a simmer. Cover and bring the heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove the lid and add the mixed vegetables. Replace the lid and cook for another 5 minutes. Fluff rice and serve.